1
00:01:25,789 --> 00:01:35,020
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,550 --> 00:01:37,940
[Episode 14]

3
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:41,190
Over here.

4
00:01:41,590 --> 00:01:42,050
Come on.

5
00:01:46,950 --> 00:01:47,680
Boss!

6
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:49,350
Boss!

7
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:52,509
Give me a hand.

8
00:01:52,509 --> 00:01:53,640
What took you so long?

9
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:55,229
I’ve been waiting so long
I’m about to get off work.

10
00:01:55,229 --> 00:01:56,780
Where is this?

11
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:59,890
I want to go back to my dorm.

12
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:01,360
[Registration Room]

13
00:02:00,060 --> 00:02:00,750
Baby,

14
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,180
we are at the dorm.

15
00:02:02,290 --> 00:02:03,590
Let me tell your teacher,

16
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:04,450
and we'll go in.

17
00:02:05,570 --> 00:02:06,350
Don't just stand there.

18
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:07,750
Hurry up and get us a room.

19
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:09,460
How much did she drink?

20
00:02:09,460 --> 00:02:10,590
Don’t stress, baby.

21
00:02:10,620 --> 00:02:11,420
Don’t stress.

22
00:02:11,460 --> 00:02:12,460
We'll go back now.

23
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,820
Don't just stand there.

24
00:02:16,710 --> 00:02:17,329
Register.

25
00:02:17,620 --> 00:02:18,090
What?

26
00:02:18,190 --> 00:02:19,450
Why should I register?

27
00:02:19,870 --> 00:02:21,420
Don't you have to register
to stay in a hotel?

28
00:02:21,420 --> 00:02:22,720
Are you kidding me?

29
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:23,840
Kidding you?

30
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,210
You’ve gotta register to check in.

31
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:31,500
[Registration Room]

32
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:27,970
Okay.

33
00:02:27,970 --> 00:02:29,060
Hurry up.

34
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:32,910
Don’t stress.

35
00:02:32,910 --> 00:02:33,840
What about hers?

36
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:36,590
We’re together.

37
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:38,250
Can’t we just register as one?

38
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,579
You two are staying in the same room?

39
00:02:40,579 --> 00:02:41,410
Obviously.

40
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:43,060
Marriage certificate.

41
00:02:43,060 --> 00:02:44,660
What marriage certificate?

42
00:02:44,930 --> 00:02:46,150
If you want to share a room,
you need a marriage certificate.

43
00:02:46,150 --> 00:02:47,810
No certificate, no same room.

44
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:48,910
Bro,

45
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,620
are you kidding me?

46
00:02:50,810 --> 00:02:51,590
Do I have nothing better to do?

47
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:52,590
Those are the rules here.

48
00:02:52,190 --> 00:02:55,380
[Registration Room]

49
00:02:52,620 --> 00:02:53,750
Those are the rules.

50
00:02:54,470 --> 00:02:54,880
No.

51
00:02:55,090 --> 00:02:55,520
Don’t put on that big-shot act

52
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,860
with me.

53
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:59,120
Watch your mouth.

54
00:02:59,790 --> 00:03:01,560
I just won’t stay here, okay?

55
00:03:04,010 --> 00:03:04,800
Fine.

56
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:06,710
You can go, but she can't.

57
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:07,560
Why?

58
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:08,620
Because she's drunk,

59
00:03:08,620 --> 00:03:10,020
and you're tricking her.

60
00:03:10,910 --> 00:03:11,810
I've seen robbers,

61
00:03:11,810 --> 00:03:13,060
but I've never seen kidnappers.

62
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:14,680
Well today I am.

63
00:03:15,370 --> 00:03:16,800
The girl wanted to go back to her dorm,

64
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,150
and you told her this is her dorm.

65
00:03:18,150 --> 00:03:18,860
Just because of this,

66
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:20,750
I can't let you take her away.

67
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:21,800
Kid,

68
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:23,930
playing dumb with me, huh?

69
00:03:24,870 --> 00:03:26,130
Believe it or not, I'll kill you!

70
00:03:26,130 --> 00:03:27,650
Are you playing tough, huh?

71
00:03:27,650 --> 00:03:28,750
My guys are all here.

72
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:29,810
What's wrong, Luo?

73
00:03:34,090 --> 00:03:35,750
Are you calling for backup, huh?

74
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:37,430
I'm not bullying you today.

75
00:03:37,590 --> 00:03:38,579
We can settle this by the book—

76
00:03:38,579 --> 00:03:39,410
go to the station.

77
00:03:39,410 --> 00:03:40,400
Tang is there.

78
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:42,010
Two options. Your call.

79
00:03:48,870 --> 00:03:50,600
Seasons Change Hostel, right?

80
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,250
I'll remember this.

81
00:03:53,590 --> 00:03:54,690
You remember it!

82
00:03:56,460 --> 00:03:57,460
Are you okay, Luo?

83
00:03:59,620 --> 00:04:00,150
I'm fine.

84
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:01,840
Go back, guys.

85
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:02,660
All right.

86
00:04:18,430 --> 00:04:19,019
Miss,

87
00:04:19,190 --> 00:04:20,649
which school are you from?

88
00:04:20,980 --> 00:04:23,380
Do you remember the school's phone number?

89
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:31,370
He just asked me to drink.

90
00:04:31,450 --> 00:04:33,330
He is not a good person.

91
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,680
Yes, yes, he's not a good person.

92
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:35,450
I can tell.

93
00:04:35,490 --> 00:04:36,270
I chased him away.

94
00:04:36,270 --> 00:04:37,000
Don't worry.

95
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:38,060
I want to throw up.

96
00:04:38,870 --> 00:04:39,980
Don't throw up on the floor.

97
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:40,500
Throw up here.

98
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:41,100
Over here.

99
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:41,920
Throw up here.

100
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:42,700
Right here.

101
00:04:42,810 --> 00:04:43,740
Not on the floor.

102
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,810
Are you feeling better?

103
00:04:58,450 --> 00:04:59,450
Sir.

104
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:02,260
I'm not a teacher.

105
00:05:02,420 --> 00:05:03,150
I'm the boss.

106
00:05:04,010 --> 00:05:05,440
Are you okay now?

107
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:08,200
-I want to sleep.
-Are you going back to school?

108
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:12,480
I want to sleep.

109
00:05:13,070 --> 00:05:14,010
Wait, I...

110
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:19,440
Come this way.

111
00:05:19,890 --> 00:05:21,120
Come on.

112
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:21,830
Slow down.

113
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,330
Easy. Come.

114
00:05:23,330 --> 00:05:23,980
Come on.

115
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:24,540
Up the stairs.

116
00:05:24,540 --> 00:05:26,290
Stairs.

117
00:05:26,510 --> 00:05:27,410
Up the stairs.

118
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:28,690
Go inside.

119
00:05:28,770 --> 00:05:29,510
Keep going.

120
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,720
This way.

121
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:33,180
Yes.

122
00:05:33,570 --> 00:05:34,570
Turn right.

123
00:06:24,540 --> 00:06:25,220
Get up!

124
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:26,540
Stop sleeping.

125
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:29,400
Who are you?

126
00:06:29,570 --> 00:06:31,030
Why did you bring me here?

127
00:06:32,470 --> 00:06:33,200
It wasn't me.

128
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,540
I didn't bring you here.

129
00:06:34,540 --> 00:06:35,620
A guy named Zhao Gang

130
00:06:35,620 --> 00:06:36,830
brought you here.

131
00:06:37,010 --> 00:06:38,140
Do you remember now?

132
00:06:39,130 --> 00:06:40,810
He made you drink a lot yesterday,

133
00:06:40,810 --> 00:06:41,810
and got you drunk.

134
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:42,930
He said my place

135
00:06:42,980 --> 00:06:44,080
was your dorm.

136
00:06:44,770 --> 00:06:45,480
He lied to you.

137
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:46,159
I saw it wasn't right,

138
00:06:46,159 --> 00:06:47,330
so I kicked him out.

139
00:06:47,430 --> 00:06:49,159
And then you wanted to throw up.

140
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:50,510
I said, "Go ahead,"

141
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:51,740
and you did…
After that you sobered up a bit.

142
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:53,220
You even called me "Sir,"

143
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:53,920
remember?

144
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,920
Then you said you wanted to sleep.

145
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:58,000
I figured you couldn’t stay outside,

146
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,430
so I let you sleep in the room.

147
00:06:59,430 --> 00:07:00,360
I stayed outside all night—

148
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,220
got eaten alive by mosquitoes.

149
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:02,260
I was outside.

150
00:07:02,390 --> 00:07:03,510
Many people can

151
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:04,230
prove it.

152
00:07:04,870 --> 00:07:05,930
Then after I woke up,

153
00:07:05,930 --> 00:07:07,390
I thought you'd need to eat.

154
00:07:07,390 --> 00:07:08,770
So I went to buy breakfast for you.

155
00:07:08,770 --> 00:07:10,430
I didn't know what you wanted,

156
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:11,870
so I bought a lot.

157
00:07:12,310 --> 00:07:13,540
You...

158
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:14,680
Hurry up and eat up.

159
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,620
Don't you have classes to attend

160
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:17,150
or something after you eat?

161
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,760
I'm going to sweep the floor.

162
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,210
Eat up.

163
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:38,800
Morning, Luo.

164
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:40,320
Are you going out?

165
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:40,940
Yes, Luo.

166
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,370
You tried to be a hero

167
00:08:25,430 --> 00:08:26,860
and look at you now.

168
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:28,570
I told you

169
00:08:28,620 --> 00:08:30,150
I wasn't trying to be a hero.

170
00:08:30,620 --> 00:08:31,820
He's taking revenge.

171
00:08:32,890 --> 00:08:33,690
Is she pretty?

172
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,850
You really are getting old.

173
00:08:39,049 --> 00:08:40,289
I already told you.

174
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,809
She's as beautiful as an angel.

175
00:08:44,510 --> 00:08:46,510
If you really have feelings for her,

176
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,950
act like a man.

177
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:49,550
Take action when you should

178
00:08:49,550 --> 00:08:50,810
and confess your love.

179
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:52,580
You should know

180
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:55,590
a girl with an oval face and phoenix eyes

181
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:57,530
is liked by more than just you.

182
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:00,940
It’s like

183
00:09:00,980 --> 00:09:03,180
Wu Xiaoshuai and Xia Tian in our script?

184
00:09:05,370 --> 00:09:07,180
The characters in the story

185
00:09:07,270 --> 00:09:08,840
have already done their best.

186
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,100
But as screenwriters,

187
00:09:10,620 --> 00:09:11,800
we must be ruthless

188
00:09:11,890 --> 00:09:12,980
and twist the ending of the story

189
00:09:12,980 --> 00:09:14,180
into something else.

190
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:17,960
Do you think

191
00:09:18,410 --> 00:09:19,820
wouldn't God dare to do

192
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:21,590
what scriptwriters dare to do?

193
00:09:23,940 --> 00:09:24,840
God

194
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:27,440
is the most ruthless scriptwriter.

195
00:09:33,370 --> 00:09:34,100
You know?

196
00:09:35,790 --> 00:09:36,250
Then...

197
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,720
The conflict between you
and Director Weng,

198
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:38,960
was it also a love rivalry?

199
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:39,270
I...

200
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:41,910
I and...

201
00:09:57,460 --> 00:09:58,130
Well...

202
00:10:02,630 --> 00:10:04,960
The girl with an oval face
and phoenix eyes

203
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:06,670
was snatched away by him.

204
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,790
Was she pretty?

205
00:10:11,850 --> 00:10:13,180
Very pretty.

206
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:15,160
Tell me.

207
00:10:15,910 --> 00:10:17,130
Tell me, tell me.

208
00:10:18,940 --> 00:10:20,070
I'm not telling you.

209
00:10:26,390 --> 00:10:27,740
Your wiring’s all worn out.

210
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:29,800
This won’t do; you need to replace it.

211
00:10:29,890 --> 00:10:30,700
Dongbei,

212
00:10:30,820 --> 00:10:32,110
you really should get your electricity

213
00:10:32,110 --> 00:10:33,120
fixed properly.

214
00:10:32,820 --> 00:10:42,060
[Guest Room]

215
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:33,860
You go out first.

216
00:10:33,860 --> 00:10:36,100
The power’ll be back
once you come back in.

217
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,010
Whether it gets replaced isn’t up to me.

218
00:10:38,010 --> 00:10:39,480
I've told the boss so many times,

219
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,740
but he doesn't listen to me.

220
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:42,270
Just make do with it for now.

221
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,550
Ranran,

222
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:46,130
in broad daylight,

223
00:10:46,130 --> 00:10:47,270
how much did you drink?

224
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:48,130
Don't touch me.

225
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:58,770
[Guest Room]

226
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:52,660
Hurry back to your room and rest.

227
00:10:53,340 --> 00:10:54,340
Drink some water.

228
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:55,690
Um, the tape.

229
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,370
Give me the tape.

230
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:04,910
What do you mean?

231
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:08,630
Wait, are you going out again

232
00:11:08,630 --> 00:11:09,430
in this state?

233
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:11,620
I’m just feeling frustrated.

234
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:13,980
Ranran!

235
00:11:14,890 --> 00:11:15,360
Zhao.

236
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,500
You shouldn't go out
when you're this drunk.

237
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:17,480
Can you fix it or not?

238
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:18,690
If not, let me fix it.

239
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,690
I’m waiting to watch TV.

240
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:21,270
Here.

241
00:11:21,370 --> 00:11:23,220
Little Northeasterner, here you go.

242
00:11:23,220 --> 00:11:23,670
Pliers.

243
00:11:23,670 --> 00:11:24,770
This month's rent.

244
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:25,700
Take it.

245
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:28,230
What are you doing?

246
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:29,430
Stop messing around.

247
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:29,910
My waist.

248
00:11:29,910 --> 00:11:31,170
Why didn't you go out for work today?

249
00:11:31,170 --> 00:11:33,070
My back is acting up again.

250
00:11:33,620 --> 00:11:34,240
Hey,

251
00:11:34,370 --> 00:11:35,300
go out for a walk.

252
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:36,520
Why?

253
00:11:37,890 --> 00:11:38,580
Ranran

254
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:40,270
drank too much.

255
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:41,470
Something feels off.

256
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:42,480
I hope nothing bad happens.

257
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,130
Go check on her.

258
00:11:43,130 --> 00:11:45,260
What's wrong? Did she audition again?

259
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:47,910
I don't understand things in your circle.

260
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:48,500
Hurry up and check on her.

261
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:49,840
She went towards the lake.

262
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:50,500
Go quickly.

263
00:12:07,820 --> 00:12:08,550
Little girl,

264
00:12:09,460 --> 00:12:11,290
it’s so early—how’d you get this drunk?

265
00:12:11,290 --> 00:12:11,760
Come on,

266
00:12:11,790 --> 00:12:12,890
let me take you somewhere to rest.

267
00:12:12,890 --> 00:12:13,450
Let's go.

268
00:12:13,630 --> 00:12:14,690
What are you doing?

269
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:16,000
Hey, who are you?

270
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,260
I... I am her uncle.

271
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:18,910
Her uncle?

272
00:12:18,910 --> 00:12:19,840
What do you want?

273
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:21,340
Fine, you are her uncle.

274
00:12:21,860 --> 00:12:23,320
You are not behaving well.

275
00:12:23,670 --> 00:12:24,670
Go home right now!

276
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:27,170
What are you wandering around for?

277
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:54,770
You sit right here.

278
00:12:55,290 --> 00:12:56,050
Don't move.

279
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:07,120
Here,

280
00:13:07,940 --> 00:13:08,870
have some water.

281
00:13:10,010 --> 00:13:11,100
It'll sober you up.

282
00:13:14,510 --> 00:13:15,460
My son

283
00:13:16,340 --> 00:13:17,940
really loves drinking this.

284
00:13:18,790 --> 00:13:22,290
No matter how sad he is,

285
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:24,940
a soda will cheer him up.

286
00:13:25,890 --> 00:13:26,700
Try it.

287
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:54,520
Tell me,

288
00:13:55,620 --> 00:13:56,150
can I

289
00:13:57,220 --> 00:13:59,240
help you?

290
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:06,760
If you really can't hold on anymore,

291
00:14:06,870 --> 00:14:07,670
just go back to your hometown.

292
00:14:06,940 --> 00:14:09,820
[Ice cream]

293
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:09,710
Go find your dad and mom.

294
00:14:09,740 --> 00:14:11,640
Why can't I hold on?

295
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,290
Why should I go back to my hometown?

296
00:14:13,290 --> 00:14:15,350
Why don’t you go back to your parents?

297
00:14:20,410 --> 00:14:20,770
Well,

298
00:14:21,270 --> 00:14:24,940
I think Beijing is pretty good.

299
00:14:25,770 --> 00:14:27,220
There’s hope here.

300
00:14:27,340 --> 00:14:28,860
I'm motivated to do anything.

301
00:14:28,860 --> 00:14:29,980
I’ve got plenty

302
00:14:29,980 --> 00:14:30,860
that I can do too.

303
00:14:30,860 --> 00:14:32,240
I'm a good actress too.

304
00:14:33,170 --> 00:14:34,580
Why make me go home?

305
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:35,410
Yes.

306
00:14:36,510 --> 00:14:38,270
We all think

307
00:14:38,270 --> 00:14:39,530
you are a good actress.

308
00:14:40,770 --> 00:14:41,220
You are

309
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:42,940
a very, very good actress.

310
00:14:50,940 --> 00:14:52,070
Don't stand there.

311
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:52,760
Have a seat.

312
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:57,890
Drink.

313
00:14:58,580 --> 00:15:00,480
Here, there's another bottle.

314
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,750
I'll put it here. Drink.

315
00:15:03,550 --> 00:15:04,190
Drink.

316
00:15:10,860 --> 00:15:12,130
You are an extra.

317
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:16,090
I want to play the leading lady.

318
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:18,890
It’s not the same; you don’t get it.

319
00:15:19,130 --> 00:15:20,610
It's a circle.

320
00:15:20,910 --> 00:15:22,070
At the very top

321
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:23,650
of this pyramid

322
00:15:23,650 --> 00:15:24,790
are the investors

323
00:15:24,820 --> 00:15:25,890
and producers.

324
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,460
Around a dinner table,

325
00:15:28,770 --> 00:15:29,860
there’s a whole circle

326
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:31,390
of girls just like me.

327
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:33,500
They all want to be actresses,

328
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:34,760
all want roles.

329
00:15:36,010 --> 00:15:38,010
And they’re even prettier than I am—

330
00:15:39,030 --> 00:15:39,890
better at talking,

331
00:15:39,890 --> 00:15:41,220
and better at drinking.

332
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:43,890
What can I do?

333
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,410
If I don't go,

334
00:15:47,410 --> 00:15:49,740
I won’t even have this little chance left.

335
00:15:49,790 --> 00:15:50,840
Since I came to Beijing,

336
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:52,270
I feel like I'm a failure.

337
00:15:52,270 --> 00:15:54,080
I haven't got a single role

338
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:57,570
and am still living in this basement.

339
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:20,480
I don't understand

340
00:16:21,150 --> 00:16:22,580
that circle

341
00:16:24,370 --> 00:16:25,260
you mentioned.

342
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:30,460
But if you want to compete,
then compete properly—

343
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:32,230
be a good actress.

344
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:34,440
Don't compete with them over

345
00:16:34,550 --> 00:16:35,870
who is more articulate

346
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,360
or can drink more.

347
00:16:37,670 --> 00:16:40,100
Just strive to be a good actress, right?

348
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,500
Anyway, all of us

349
00:16:44,050 --> 00:16:46,100
think you are a good actress.

350
00:16:47,790 --> 00:16:48,460
Besides,

351
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:50,670
if hanging out with them

352
00:16:50,670 --> 00:16:51,730
makes you unhappy,

353
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:54,300
then don't hang out with them.

354
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:56,440
You can stay with us.

355
00:16:56,650 --> 00:16:57,140
Right?

356
00:16:57,630 --> 00:16:59,830
You come back to Seasons Change Hostel.

357
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:01,720
It's so nice here.

358
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:04,560
You have Zhuang Zhuang

359
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:05,730
here, right?

360
00:17:05,770 --> 00:17:06,550
There's Xu,

361
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:08,220
Cao,

362
00:17:08,690 --> 00:17:10,160
and Liangliang.

363
00:17:13,980 --> 00:17:15,240
With all these people,

364
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:16,920
wouldn't you be happy?

365
00:17:21,829 --> 00:17:24,569
You say I'm an extra.

366
00:17:25,980 --> 00:17:27,109
But I have lines.

367
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:30,080
I'm a guest actor.

368
00:17:30,380 --> 00:17:31,900
My line goes like this,

369
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:37,780
"Charge!"

370
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:42,690
This "Charge!"

371
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:44,790
has helped me a lot.

372
00:17:45,660 --> 00:17:46,680
Every time

373
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:48,180
I encounter difficulties,

374
00:17:48,180 --> 00:17:48,920
I just think,

375
00:17:50,750 --> 00:17:52,160
"Charge!"

376
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:57,680
But kid,

377
00:17:58,700 --> 00:17:59,740
everything

378
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:02,110
has a limit.

379
00:18:03,010 --> 00:18:05,010
When I first came to Beijing,

380
00:18:05,220 --> 00:18:06,020
I thought that

381
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:08,390
as an extra

382
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,820
I could make a few dozen yuan a day,

383
00:18:11,110 --> 00:18:12,420
and after a month

384
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:15,080
I’d have over a thousand.

385
00:18:15,220 --> 00:18:17,510
If I just stuck with it for a few years,

386
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:20,590
wouldn’t I reach my goal?

387
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:25,030
I was being too optimistic.

388
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:28,110
After a month,

389
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,930
there’s barely any work at all.

390
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:32,760
But I couldn’t just sit around like that,

391
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,770
so I started wandering everywhere
looking for work.

392
00:18:34,770 --> 00:18:37,240
One day I passed by a construction site.

393
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:41,090
They were carrying cement bags,

394
00:18:41,510 --> 00:18:42,310
so I asked

395
00:18:42,310 --> 00:18:43,610
how much it paid.

396
00:18:44,660 --> 00:18:45,770
They said,

397
00:18:46,090 --> 00:18:47,210
"Thirty yuan

398
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:48,630
a day.

399
00:18:48,850 --> 00:18:50,290
Are you in or not?"

400
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:53,250
I thought it over and over

401
00:18:55,480 --> 00:18:56,480
and still said no.

402
00:18:57,830 --> 00:19:00,000
I still have two mouths to feed.

403
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:02,900
So I can't risk my life
just to make money.

404
00:19:03,530 --> 00:19:04,280
Beijing has

405
00:19:05,030 --> 00:19:06,480
so many opportunities.

406
00:19:07,570 --> 00:19:08,890
There's a lot of work,

407
00:19:09,110 --> 00:19:10,420
so there's hope.

408
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:13,860
In a person's heart,

409
00:19:15,290 --> 00:19:17,540
there must be a line.

410
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:19,790
Right?

411
00:19:21,290 --> 00:19:22,550
There must be a line.

412
00:19:32,310 --> 00:19:33,640
Are you falling asleep?

413
00:20:08,180 --> 00:20:09,840
Master, please wait a moment.

414
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:12,180
The water is coming right up.

415
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:14,970
Here.

416
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:21,720
Sheng...

417
00:20:22,610 --> 00:20:23,330
Shengli.

418
00:20:28,930 --> 00:20:35,740
Shengli, this time
I really can't see anything.

419
00:20:41,830 --> 00:20:43,010
Master,

420
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:45,670
are you hungry?

421
00:20:46,220 --> 00:20:47,660
I'll go cook for you.

422
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:48,240
Okay.

423
00:20:57,850 --> 00:20:59,480
Master, dinner is ready.

424
00:20:59,590 --> 00:20:59,940
Okay.

425
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:02,040
Okay.

426
00:21:03,140 --> 00:21:04,730
Today's dishes include

427
00:21:05,380 --> 00:21:06,380
braised chicken,

428
00:21:07,290 --> 00:21:09,070
and pork stewed with potatoes.

429
00:21:09,070 --> 00:21:09,570
Okay.

430
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:12,080
Stir-fried sweet potato leaves.

431
00:21:12,350 --> 00:21:13,660
And twice-cooked pork.

432
00:21:13,660 --> 00:21:14,880
Okay.

433
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:18,000
Here are your chopsticks.

434
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,350
Okay.

435
00:21:28,090 --> 00:21:28,440
Here.

436
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:30,090
Okay.

437
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:32,550
Okay.

438
00:21:33,110 --> 00:21:33,590
Okay.

439
00:21:34,110 --> 00:21:35,290
Okay.

440
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:39,350
Okay.

441
00:21:42,550 --> 00:21:44,420
I’ll get you some more
sweet potato leaves.

442
00:21:44,420 --> 00:21:44,750
Here.

443
00:21:44,980 --> 00:21:46,330
Okay.

444
00:21:49,050 --> 00:21:50,180
Twice-cooked pork.

445
00:21:52,530 --> 00:21:53,990
The boss at the market said

446
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:56,430
your favorite sweet potato leaves

447
00:21:56,550 --> 00:21:57,880
are going out of season.

448
00:21:58,610 --> 00:21:59,660
But it's fine.

449
00:22:00,290 --> 00:22:02,000
It doesn't matter
if the sweet potato leaves are gone.

450
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:02,680
There will be

451
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:04,510
better vegetables on the market later.

452
00:22:04,510 --> 00:22:05,240
Is that so?

453
00:22:07,590 --> 00:22:11,140
It's so hard just to

454
00:22:11,610 --> 00:22:12,940
have a meal in this life.

455
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:21,830
I'll cook for you anytime you want.

456
00:22:22,050 --> 00:22:23,380
Okay.

457
00:22:30,090 --> 00:22:31,260
Today I added

458
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,800
the stories about you and Director Weng

459
00:22:35,010 --> 00:22:36,160
to our script.

460
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:38,140
Do you think Director Weng

461
00:22:38,140 --> 00:22:39,530
will be mad at me?

462
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:40,410
Go ahead,

463
00:22:41,220 --> 00:22:41,620
add it.

464
00:22:43,220 --> 00:22:44,450
Do you really think

465
00:22:44,830 --> 00:22:46,360
we’ve been holding a grudge

466
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,140
over something that small

467
00:22:48,980 --> 00:22:50,290
for 20 years?

468
00:22:53,140 --> 00:22:54,420
Then why is it?

469
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:01,550
Because that brat

470
00:23:02,740 --> 00:23:04,400
messed around with my script!

471
00:23:10,330 --> 00:23:10,980
Eat.

472
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:12,110
Eat.

473
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:19,090
Okay.

474
00:23:21,420 --> 00:23:22,080
Delicious.

475
00:23:27,460 --> 00:23:29,400
Didn't I alter your script too?

476
00:23:30,660 --> 00:23:32,180
Yes, you altered it well.

477
00:23:43,550 --> 00:23:44,130
Shengli,

478
00:23:48,980 --> 00:23:50,830
pick up a piece of potato for me

479
00:23:55,530 --> 00:23:57,180
and put it in my mouth.

480
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:07,510
This is authentic.

481
00:24:12,830 --> 00:24:15,180
Is it easy to get a full meal?

482
00:24:34,940 --> 00:24:35,730
My mom said

483
00:24:35,810 --> 00:24:36,940
to wash this one too.

484
00:24:37,500 --> 00:24:37,880
Okay.

485
00:24:38,710 --> 00:24:45,870
[Professional Repair
of All Home Appliances]

486
00:24:39,010 --> 00:24:39,670
Put it here.

487
00:24:45,310 --> 00:24:46,480
What grade are you in?

488
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:47,340
Seventh grade.

489
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:49,650
You're about the same age as my son.

490
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:51,030
You just finished your exams, right?

491
00:24:51,030 --> 00:24:51,940
How did you do?

492
00:24:55,140 --> 00:24:56,660
My son's grades

493
00:24:56,810 --> 00:24:57,860
are really good.

494
00:24:59,030 --> 00:25:00,290
Why do you talk so much?

495
00:25:00,690 --> 00:25:02,970
[Professional Repair
of All Home Appliances]

496
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:07,070
You're not good at studying, huh?

497
00:25:11,090 --> 00:25:12,230
I haven't seen them

498
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:13,830
for half a year.

499
00:25:23,270 --> 00:25:23,790
Master,

500
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:25,330
if you go back to recover

501
00:25:25,330 --> 00:25:26,140
and need an extra hand,

502
00:25:26,140 --> 00:25:27,340
I'll go back with you.

503
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:30,040
The factory will send someone
to escort me.

504
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:31,790
If you go,

505
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:34,720
who’s going to take care of
your food and lodging? It’ll cost money.

506
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,330
I can take care of myself.

507
00:25:37,500 --> 00:25:38,570
I knew even if I told you,

508
00:25:38,570 --> 00:25:39,700
you wouldn’t agree.

509
00:25:41,380 --> 00:25:42,770
Good delivery.

510
00:25:42,980 --> 00:25:44,480
One line, two meanings—

511
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:45,160
clever.

512
00:25:45,380 --> 00:25:46,780
I'm not lying.

513
00:25:47,010 --> 00:25:47,770
Just say the word,

514
00:25:47,770 --> 00:25:49,030
and I'll be right over.

515
00:25:50,660 --> 00:25:52,940
You... You have a lame leg,

516
00:25:53,090 --> 00:25:54,440
and I'm blind.

517
00:25:54,740 --> 00:25:56,560
If we stand on the street,

518
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:58,530
people will think we're beggars.

519
00:25:58,590 --> 00:25:59,720
Isn't that perfect?

520
00:26:00,010 --> 00:26:01,160
I'll get you an erhu.

521
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:02,220
We can earn our travel expenses

522
00:26:02,220 --> 00:26:03,020
along the way.

523
00:26:05,610 --> 00:26:08,140
I really don't need more hands right now.

524
00:26:09,350 --> 00:26:11,810
What I'm most worried about

525
00:26:12,090 --> 00:26:13,120
is just one thing.

526
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:13,930
Don't worry.

527
00:26:14,810 --> 00:26:16,440
I’ll get it done—
on time and up to standard.

528
00:26:16,440 --> 00:26:18,330
You’re still missing a word… "well."

529
00:26:18,330 --> 00:26:19,550
I’ll get it done well—

530
00:26:19,550 --> 00:26:21,140
on time and up to standard.

531
00:26:22,330 --> 00:26:24,390
What I’m really worried about is you.

532
00:26:25,380 --> 00:26:26,440
Once you get there,

533
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:27,510
let me know you're safe.

534
00:26:27,510 --> 00:26:28,310
Stop nagging.

535
00:26:29,740 --> 00:26:31,000
After I left,

536
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:33,230
since your leg is bad,

537
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:34,500
you can stay here.

538
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:36,450
After you finish the draft,

539
00:26:36,660 --> 00:26:38,600
copy it out

540
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:39,830
neatly and properly

541
00:26:40,330 --> 00:26:41,790
and give me your feedback.

542
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:43,920
Who’d dare give you feedback?

543
00:26:44,830 --> 00:26:46,490
But I don't mind staying here.

544
00:26:48,700 --> 00:26:51,500
A young upstart can always
surprise an old master.

545
00:26:51,940 --> 00:26:53,200
You need to toughen up.

546
00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:54,100
Alright.

547
00:26:54,500 --> 00:26:55,630
Walk me downstairs.

548
00:26:57,850 --> 00:26:58,700
Toughen up.

549
00:27:01,310 --> 00:27:03,670
You must take good care of my books.

550
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:06,310
Read more.

551
00:27:06,570 --> 00:27:08,560
You can only improve by reading.

552
00:27:09,180 --> 00:27:09,660
Got it.

553
00:27:10,940 --> 00:27:11,660
Shengli.

554
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:14,820
It's not like you're not coming back.

555
00:27:15,010 --> 00:27:17,010
Why are you bringing so many things?

556
00:27:17,070 --> 00:27:18,200
I'll keep your books

557
00:27:18,310 --> 00:27:19,330
and read them.

558
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:22,590
Who said I would definitely come back?

559
00:27:23,530 --> 00:27:25,060
What are you talking about?

560
00:27:25,070 --> 00:27:26,220
Once you’ve gotten used to
stuffed beef pancakes,

561
00:27:26,220 --> 00:27:27,700
plain steamed buns just
don’t go down anymore, right?

562
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:28,410
Exactly.

563
00:27:28,570 --> 00:27:29,660
A nobody suddenly acting like a big shot

564
00:27:29,660 --> 00:27:30,610
after getting a bit of luck.

565
00:27:30,610 --> 00:27:31,870
Who can we complain to?

566
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:34,060
There's nothing we can do.

567
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:34,970
This

568
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:36,270
is fate.

569
00:27:37,070 --> 00:27:37,500
Look,

570
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:38,690
people say

571
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:40,590
when one person reaches enlightenment,

572
00:27:40,590 --> 00:27:41,680
even their whole household benefits.

573
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:42,070
No...

574
00:27:42,070 --> 00:27:44,470
-You’re bringing us along too?
-No, no, no.

575
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:46,600
You want to get benefits?

576
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:48,160
Be glad I didn’t drag you

577
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:49,050
straight down instead.

578
00:27:49,050 --> 00:27:50,980
What? The eighteen levels of hell?

579
00:27:51,270 --> 00:27:52,400
Are you done?

580
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:52,790
We're already

581
00:27:52,790 --> 00:27:54,510
on the first level underground.

582
00:27:54,510 --> 00:27:56,110
Seventeen more levels to go?

583
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,980
Look at you all,

584
00:27:58,070 --> 00:27:59,220
all talk.

585
00:27:59,610 --> 00:28:01,260
Can you take some real action

586
00:28:01,290 --> 00:28:02,250
to show it?

587
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:03,140
Show what?

588
00:28:05,090 --> 00:28:06,640
Let's give him a hug.

589
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:08,270
Come, hug.

590
00:28:08,270 --> 00:28:08,940
Sure.

591
00:28:08,940 --> 00:28:09,610
Just say it,

592
00:28:09,610 --> 00:28:10,310
I'll give you a hug.

593
00:28:10,310 --> 00:28:11,700
No.

594
00:28:11,940 --> 00:28:12,750
You want a hug?

595
00:28:14,280 --> 00:28:15,850
I'll hug you first.

596
00:28:15,940 --> 00:28:17,340
Who’s going to hug first?

597
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:18,240
Hug him right here.

598
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:19,100
Give him a kiss.

599
00:28:19,590 --> 00:28:20,830
Come, give him a kiss.

600
00:28:20,830 --> 00:28:22,430
-I mean parting wine
-Get up.

601
00:28:22,460 --> 00:28:24,180
-and farewell dishes.
-Give you a hug.

602
00:28:24,180 --> 00:28:24,830
What?

603
00:28:24,940 --> 00:28:25,610
No,

604
00:28:26,310 --> 00:28:27,250
you're overthinking.

605
00:28:27,250 --> 00:28:29,090
I’m broke. My pockets are empty.

606
00:28:29,110 --> 00:28:30,570
I really don't have money.

607
00:28:30,590 --> 00:28:31,670
No.

608
00:28:31,810 --> 00:28:32,960
Look at you all,

609
00:28:33,050 --> 00:28:35,140
-Open the door!
-You ungrateful jerk.

610
00:28:35,140 --> 00:28:36,680
-Coming.
-Come on. Give me a hand.

611
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:37,270
Coming.

612
00:28:39,530 --> 00:28:40,660
The dishes are here.

613
00:28:41,250 --> 00:28:43,070
I had Little Northeasterner prepare it.

614
00:28:43,070 --> 00:28:43,640
How is it?

615
00:28:44,830 --> 00:28:46,770
So we all benefit, right?

616
00:28:48,750 --> 00:28:51,970
Alright then, we’ll benefit together!

617
00:28:52,090 --> 00:28:52,960
Come.

618
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:54,860
Hold on, let me check first

619
00:28:55,030 --> 00:28:56,350
whether this wine is any good

620
00:28:56,350 --> 00:28:57,240
and whether the food’s decent.

621
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:58,440
Look, is this wine...

622
00:28:58,440 --> 00:28:59,420
Take a look.

623
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:02,440
It's good wine.

624
00:29:02,920 --> 00:29:03,350
Okay.

625
00:29:03,610 --> 00:29:04,740
Okay, okay, come on.

626
00:29:05,570 --> 00:29:07,510
Let's drink until he can't leave today.

627
00:29:07,510 --> 00:29:08,310
Get him drunk.

628
00:29:08,610 --> 00:29:09,700
Yeah, get him drunk.

629
00:29:09,700 --> 00:29:10,590
Just get him drunk.

630
00:29:10,590 --> 00:29:11,750
We have to get him drunk today.

631
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:13,680
It's hard to say who's getting who drunk.

632
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:15,080
Who's getting who drunk?

633
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:16,680
Are they getting you drunk?

634
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,960
Th-they want to get me drunk.

635
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:19,570
No, we wouldn't dare.

636
00:29:19,590 --> 00:29:21,110
Someone is protecting him now,

637
00:29:21,110 --> 00:29:21,570
right?

638
00:29:21,740 --> 00:29:23,550
If things go wrong,
she’ll flip the table on us.

639
00:29:23,550 --> 00:29:24,050
Right?

640
00:29:24,050 --> 00:29:24,910
You haven't eaten yet, have you?

641
00:29:24,910 --> 00:29:25,850
I'm not eating.

642
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:27,510
I'll wait to eat with Ranran.

643
00:29:27,510 --> 00:29:28,880
Her stomach
hasn't been feeling well lately.

644
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:30,610
What's wrong with Ranran? What happened?

645
00:29:30,610 --> 00:29:32,700
It's nothing serious. Don't worry.

646
00:29:32,750 --> 00:29:34,220
Does it have anything to do with you?

647
00:29:34,220 --> 00:29:36,110
Does it have anything to do with you?

648
00:29:36,110 --> 00:29:36,900
I don't want

649
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:37,720
to eat with them anyway.

650
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:38,790
-Let’s eat out.
-You…

651
00:29:38,790 --> 00:29:39,270
Okay.

652
00:29:39,790 --> 00:29:40,390
All right.

653
00:29:41,250 --> 00:29:42,200
Do you guys want anything to eat?

654
00:29:42,200 --> 00:29:42,700
No, thanks.

655
00:29:42,700 --> 00:29:44,750
Xu Shengli puts girls before his friends.

656
00:29:44,750 --> 00:29:46,270
You guys can go.

657
00:29:46,270 --> 00:29:46,550
Let's go.

658
00:29:46,550 --> 00:29:46,900
Go.

659
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:49,640
Bring some millet porridge for Ranran.

660
00:29:50,110 --> 00:29:51,250
You're not being polite at all.

661
00:29:51,250 --> 00:29:52,090
I'll go make it for you?

662
00:29:52,090 --> 00:29:53,900
If we don't make him drunk now,
then who will?

663
00:29:53,900 --> 00:29:55,110
-You.
-Make you drunk.

664
00:29:55,110 --> 00:29:56,480
Don't make me drunk.

665
00:29:59,530 --> 00:30:00,190
Are you sad?

666
00:30:01,070 --> 00:30:01,930
Sad about what?

667
00:30:03,460 --> 00:30:05,520
Aren't you sad that I'm leaving here?

668
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:10,670
What if I never come back?

669
00:30:11,050 --> 00:30:13,330
Life goes on with or without anyone.

670
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:15,750
Be careful.

671
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:18,320
Sit for a while.

672
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:19,470
Don't worry.

673
00:30:19,660 --> 00:30:21,260
I will definitely come back.

674
00:30:27,310 --> 00:30:28,770
People always aim higher.

675
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:30,690
I just hope you don’t come back.

676
00:30:31,510 --> 00:30:33,000
There you go again.

677
00:30:33,950 --> 00:30:35,680
But what will you do without me?

678
00:30:35,740 --> 00:30:37,000
I won't let myself starve.

679
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:37,460
Then...

680
00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:40,220
What if others bully you?

681
00:30:43,590 --> 00:30:44,390
Don't worry.

682
00:30:44,940 --> 00:30:46,140
I can go to the police.

683
00:30:50,290 --> 00:30:52,520
I just want you to focus

684
00:30:52,660 --> 00:30:54,390
and write your script in peace.

685
00:30:54,770 --> 00:30:55,420
Everyone is waiting

686
00:30:55,420 --> 00:30:56,480
to watch your movie.

687
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:58,080
It wouldn't delay anything.

688
00:30:58,220 --> 00:30:59,550
I didn't say it would.

689
00:31:00,420 --> 00:31:03,880
It's not like we'll never see each other
again after you leave.

690
00:31:08,660 --> 00:31:09,790
Will you come see me?

691
00:31:18,380 --> 00:31:20,480
I'll have to see how your recovery goes.

692
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:22,140
Don't try to pin it on me later.

693
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:29,850
Well, my leg

694
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:31,010
isn't healed yet.

695
00:31:31,070 --> 00:31:32,790
Doesn't that mean you have to

696
00:31:32,790 --> 00:31:33,850
take care of me now?

697
00:31:35,220 --> 00:31:35,640
You...

698
00:32:04,180 --> 00:32:04,620
I...

699
00:32:05,740 --> 00:32:06,480
I sincerely hope

700
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:07,950
you can use this good luck

701
00:32:08,030 --> 00:32:09,360
to keep getting better.

702
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:15,670
We will both

703
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:17,760
get better and better together.

704
00:32:25,700 --> 00:32:26,110
Okay.

705
00:32:36,550 --> 00:32:40,900
I've searched for you
over thousands of miles.

706
00:32:43,180 --> 00:32:45,310
Without a care.

707
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:46,090
Hello, sir.

708
00:32:46,140 --> 00:32:46,680
I'm not...

709
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:50,570
You don't seem to be in my dreams.

710
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:55,920
But in my dreams you are my only one.

711
00:32:56,660 --> 00:32:57,610
Hello, sir.

712
00:32:58,310 --> 00:32:58,770
Hello.

713
00:32:59,810 --> 00:33:00,660
Are you

714
00:33:00,900 --> 00:33:01,560
a director?

715
00:33:01,610 --> 00:33:02,070
No.

716
00:33:02,750 --> 00:33:04,010
I'm the screenwriter.

717
00:33:04,500 --> 00:33:05,330
No wonder

718
00:33:05,610 --> 00:33:06,240
I haven’t even gotten close

719
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:07,750
to you yet,

720
00:33:07,750 --> 00:33:09,660
this strong cultural vibe

721
00:33:09,660 --> 00:33:11,520
is already hitting me in the face.

722
00:33:12,550 --> 00:33:13,150
Thank you.

723
00:33:13,530 --> 00:33:14,730
You live in this room?

724
00:33:15,070 --> 00:33:15,610
Yes.

725
00:33:17,330 --> 00:33:19,060
Could I have your phone number?

726
00:33:21,110 --> 00:33:22,510
I don't have a phone here.

727
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:23,890
It's fine.

728
00:33:24,070 --> 00:33:25,870
Then I'll leave you to your work.

729
00:33:42,380 --> 00:33:42,940
Sir,

730
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:45,200
I actually really like literature too.

731
00:33:45,900 --> 00:33:47,160
When you have time,

732
00:33:47,660 --> 00:33:49,220
I'd like to ask for your advice.

733
00:33:49,220 --> 00:33:50,110
Would that be okay?

734
00:33:50,110 --> 00:33:51,270
Sure, no problem.

735
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:53,020
Sir, I'll be leaving now.

736
00:33:53,020 --> 00:33:53,400
Okay.

737
00:33:53,460 --> 00:33:53,990
Goodbye.

738
00:33:54,310 --> 00:33:54,840
Goodbye.

739
00:34:12,250 --> 00:34:14,550
[At the gate of the textile factory]

740
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:19,820
[Greeting]

741
00:34:20,960 --> 00:34:21,710
[Greeting]

742
00:34:25,090 --> 00:34:25,570
Ranran,

743
00:34:26,460 --> 00:34:27,190
are you okay?

744
00:34:41,860 --> 00:34:42,790
If you were dead,

745
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:44,300
could you still make a sound?

746
00:34:44,300 --> 00:34:45,710
I'm sorry, Director.

747
00:34:51,219 --> 00:34:52,219
[Belated Love]

748
00:35:04,590 --> 00:35:07,910
[Belated Love—Xu's Version]

749
00:35:08,260 --> 00:35:13,610
Xu, toughen up!

750
00:35:20,610 --> 00:35:22,050
Speaking...

751
00:35:25,820 --> 00:35:26,370
Sir,

752
00:35:27,650 --> 00:35:28,710
are you home alone?

753
00:35:29,480 --> 00:35:30,610
Have you had dinner?

754
00:35:31,260 --> 00:35:31,880
Not yet.

755
00:35:32,190 --> 00:35:33,230
You work hard on your writing.

756
00:35:33,230 --> 00:35:34,490
You should eat on time.

757
00:35:34,710 --> 00:35:35,570
If you haven't eaten,

758
00:35:35,570 --> 00:35:36,690
let me treat you to dinner.

759
00:35:36,690 --> 00:35:37,150
No need.

760
00:35:37,550 --> 00:35:38,610
I have things to do.

761
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:39,920
I haven't eaten either.

762
00:35:39,920 --> 00:35:40,590
Let's eat together.

763
00:35:40,590 --> 00:35:42,170
No, there's really no need.

764
00:35:42,170 --> 00:35:42,940
I need to write my script.

765
00:35:42,940 --> 00:35:44,090
A meal won't take

766
00:35:44,090 --> 00:35:44,980
too much time.

767
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:46,130
Let's eat together.

768
00:35:46,130 --> 00:35:47,610
I just got inspired;

769
00:35:47,630 --> 00:35:49,160
I need to finish it quickly.

770
00:35:50,230 --> 00:35:52,420
Okay, then you keep working
on your writing.

771
00:35:52,420 --> 00:35:54,480
I'll treat you next time you're free.

772
00:36:06,820 --> 00:36:08,350
I'm really not going to eat.

773
00:36:09,090 --> 00:36:10,150
You're not eating?

774
00:36:10,860 --> 00:36:11,300
Eat!

775
00:36:11,820 --> 00:36:12,650
Eat!

776
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:15,460
I was just reading lines.

777
00:36:15,550 --> 00:36:16,700
Hurry, come in.

778
00:36:22,670 --> 00:36:23,970
This place is not bad.

779
00:36:24,730 --> 00:36:26,130
You keep it pretty clean.

780
00:36:26,300 --> 00:36:27,500
Of course.

781
00:36:27,860 --> 00:36:28,880
I cleaned it up

782
00:36:28,880 --> 00:36:30,140
all by myself.

783
00:36:30,550 --> 00:36:32,110
I'm not a slob.

784
00:36:32,670 --> 00:36:34,440
That mess in Room 108
has nothing to do with me.

785
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:35,900
Those three made the mess.

786
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,850
You’ll see when you go back.

787
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,300
Room 108 has changed.

788
00:36:44,190 --> 00:36:44,920
Changed how?

789
00:36:45,300 --> 00:36:47,090
Someone who is a neat freak moved in.

790
00:36:47,090 --> 00:36:49,890
The floor is mopped so clean
you can do splits on it.

791
00:36:51,070 --> 00:36:52,000
Isn't that good?

792
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,190
Do you have chopsticks?

793
00:36:54,190 --> 00:36:55,390
Yes, I'll go get them.

794
00:37:01,670 --> 00:37:02,070
Here.

795
00:37:07,530 --> 00:37:09,320
Such a rich meal.

796
00:37:09,460 --> 00:37:10,880
I was cooking for myself.

797
00:37:10,940 --> 00:37:12,170
I accidentally made too much

798
00:37:12,170 --> 00:37:15,300
and couldn't finish it,
so I brought it to share with you.

799
00:37:16,420 --> 00:37:18,340
You accidentally made this much?

800
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:25,530
Wenzhou food is sweet.

801
00:37:25,820 --> 00:37:27,050
I don't know if you're used to it.

802
00:37:27,050 --> 00:37:28,050
I am.

803
00:37:29,570 --> 00:37:29,980
Try it.

804
00:37:31,400 --> 00:37:32,330
It's delicious!

805
00:37:32,690 --> 00:37:33,860
Is your leg feeling better?

806
00:37:33,860 --> 00:37:34,460
It's fine.

807
00:37:35,460 --> 00:37:37,120
Watch me hop a couple of times.

808
00:37:39,130 --> 00:37:40,150
Don't end up lying on the ground

809
00:37:40,150 --> 00:37:41,280
and unable to get up.

810
00:37:43,670 --> 00:37:44,570
Stop acting.

811
00:37:44,820 --> 00:37:45,530
No, this...

812
00:37:49,710 --> 00:37:51,370
You actually pulled a muscle?

813
00:37:51,910 --> 00:37:52,730
No.

814
00:37:52,760 --> 00:37:53,210
Help me up.

815
00:37:53,210 --> 00:37:55,230
Try walking back and forth.

816
00:37:59,420 --> 00:38:00,400
I'm fine now.

817
00:38:04,760 --> 00:38:05,820
Why are you a screenwriter?

818
00:38:05,820 --> 00:38:07,080
You should be an actor.

819
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:11,400
This dish is good.

820
00:38:11,510 --> 00:38:12,240
Really good.

821
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,340
Hurry, you should eat too.

822
00:38:14,420 --> 00:38:14,860
Hurry.

823
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:17,360
Sir,

824
00:38:17,460 --> 00:38:19,590
I got you some food from the cafeteria.

825
00:38:20,760 --> 00:38:22,340
I'm eating.

826
00:38:24,340 --> 00:38:25,670
Oh, you’ve got company?

827
00:38:26,590 --> 00:38:27,940
Then let’s eat together—

828
00:38:27,940 --> 00:38:30,000
I’ll add a couple more dishes for you.

829
00:38:37,940 --> 00:38:40,390
Well, I have class.

830
00:38:40,460 --> 00:38:41,170
You guys eat.

831
00:38:41,170 --> 00:38:42,400
No, no. Zhuang Zhuang.

832
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:44,460
-I’m going to be late.
-She won't eat?

833
00:38:45,500 --> 00:38:46,400
So many dishes...

834
00:38:46,400 --> 00:38:47,260
Zhuang Zhuang!

835
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:48,660
Zhuang Zhuang.

836
00:38:49,860 --> 00:38:51,070
You misunderstood.

837
00:38:51,860 --> 00:38:53,060
Misunderstood what?

838
00:38:53,130 --> 00:38:54,940
She and I...

839
00:38:57,630 --> 00:38:58,440
Aren't you helping Mr. He

840
00:38:58,440 --> 00:38:59,280
look after the place?

841
00:38:59,280 --> 00:38:59,880
Go on then.

842
00:39:01,190 --> 00:39:02,520
Don't keep her waiting.

843
00:39:13,590 --> 00:39:14,520
Stop doing that.

844
00:39:14,690 --> 00:39:15,290
You can leave.

845
00:39:15,290 --> 00:39:16,850
Why did your friend leave?

846
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:17,500
You have so many dishes.

847
00:39:17,500 --> 00:39:18,900
We can't finish them all.

848
00:39:19,260 --> 00:39:20,320
You're not eating?

849
00:39:21,050 --> 00:39:23,310
Why are you asking when you already know?

850
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:27,160
Then I won't bother you anymore.

851
00:39:30,960 --> 00:39:31,400
Wait.

852
00:39:42,860 --> 00:39:43,340
Take it.

853
00:39:43,780 --> 00:39:45,110
Don't let it go to waste.

854
00:39:46,730 --> 00:39:47,300
Goodbye.

855
00:40:01,800 --> 00:40:02,400
Thank you.

856
00:40:07,090 --> 00:40:07,690
Thank you.

857
00:40:15,010 --> 00:40:15,540
Hey, man,

858
00:40:15,820 --> 00:40:16,710
you can take my seat.

859
00:40:16,710 --> 00:40:17,910
I'm getting off soon.

860
00:40:18,940 --> 00:40:19,600
Have a seat.

861
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:20,980
Thank you.

862
00:40:21,150 --> 00:40:21,810
No problem.

863
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:50,300
Sir,

864
00:40:51,010 --> 00:40:52,400
can we switch seats?

865
00:40:52,630 --> 00:40:53,550
Don't you have a seat?

866
00:40:53,550 --> 00:40:54,420
Just sit there.

867
00:40:54,710 --> 00:40:56,000
We know each other.

868
00:40:57,170 --> 00:40:57,710
Do you?

869
00:41:02,820 --> 00:41:03,530
Wait, I mean,

870
00:41:03,530 --> 00:41:04,280
why are you young people

871
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:05,150
up to no good like this?

872
00:41:05,150 --> 00:41:06,400
No, it's not like that.

873
00:41:06,400 --> 00:41:07,030
Conductor!

874
00:41:07,030 --> 00:41:07,670
No.

875
00:41:07,710 --> 00:41:08,500
Sir.

876
00:41:09,380 --> 00:41:10,440
We know each other.

877
00:41:10,820 --> 00:41:11,500
We do.

878
00:41:11,650 --> 00:41:12,490
You really do?

879
00:41:12,550 --> 00:41:13,420
Yes, we do.

880
00:41:15,190 --> 00:41:16,230
You're a young couple having a spat,

881
00:41:16,230 --> 00:41:17,960
and you're making a fool out of me.

882
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:18,860
Thanks, sir.

883
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:26,410
You're so good to me.

884
00:41:27,550 --> 00:41:28,570
Save it.

885
00:41:30,690 --> 00:41:32,570
I really didn't know

886
00:41:32,570 --> 00:41:34,260
that woman yesterday.

887
00:41:34,420 --> 00:41:35,440
She even delivered the food

888
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:36,500
right to your door.

889
00:41:37,570 --> 00:41:38,670
I guess

890
00:41:38,730 --> 00:41:40,830
she thought I was a teacher,

891
00:41:40,960 --> 00:41:41,630
or a professor.

892
00:41:41,630 --> 00:41:42,760
That's because I stayed in that room.

893
00:41:42,760 --> 00:41:43,470
So she...

894
00:41:45,420 --> 00:41:45,880
Sorry.

895
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:46,800
It's okay.

896
00:41:53,420 --> 00:41:55,100
You care about me that much?

897
00:41:57,670 --> 00:41:59,470
I just didn't want to waste food.

898
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:01,300
If you had told me someone
was bringing you food,

899
00:42:01,300 --> 00:42:02,700
I wouldn't have had to...

900
00:42:03,820 --> 00:42:05,980
You went to the market so early

901
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:06,830
to cook for me?

902
00:42:07,130 --> 00:42:08,530
Don't flatter yourself.

903
00:42:12,940 --> 00:42:13,980
After you left,

904
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:15,140
I had no appetite.

905
00:42:16,170 --> 00:42:17,670
I put the food

906
00:42:18,070 --> 00:42:19,170
in the fridge.

907
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:20,880
I couldn't sleep
in the middle of the night,

908
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:22,210
so I got up and had a bite.

909
00:42:22,610 --> 00:42:24,210
Once I started, I couldn't stop.

910
00:42:24,210 --> 00:42:25,510
I ate until I was stuffed.

911
00:42:25,510 --> 00:42:27,770
There wasn't a single grain of rice left.

912
00:42:28,230 --> 00:42:29,130
Are you a mouse?

913
00:42:29,710 --> 00:42:31,640
You got up in the middle of the night

914
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:33,570
to eat rice and didn't leave
a single grain?

915
00:42:33,570 --> 00:42:35,320
Well, I had to be full

916
00:42:35,380 --> 00:42:37,440
to figure out how to explain it to you.

917
00:42:38,030 --> 00:42:38,610
It's true.

918
00:42:38,610 --> 00:42:39,380
Even when analyzing a script,

919
00:42:39,380 --> 00:42:41,710
I've never weighed my words so carefully.

920
00:42:42,820 --> 00:42:43,880
You care that much?

921
00:42:44,570 --> 00:42:45,990
Of course I care.

922
00:42:46,070 --> 00:42:48,000
I couldn't let you misunderstand.

923
00:42:50,400 --> 00:42:52,510
Laugh if you want to.

924
00:42:52,710 --> 00:42:53,690
I don't want to.
